===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|verray}}, {{m|enm|verrai|t=true}}, from {{der|en|fro|verai|t=true}} (Modern {{cog|fr|vrai}}), from assumed {{der|en|VL.||vērācus}}, alteration of {{der|en|la|vērāx|t=truthful}}, from {{m|la|vērus|t=true}}, ultimately from {{der|en|ine-pro|*weh₁-|t=true, benevolent}}. Cognate with {{cog|ang|wǣr|t=true, correct}}, {{cog|nl|waar|t=true}}, {{cog|de|wahr|t=true}}, {{cog|is|alvöru|t=earnest}}. Displaced native {{cog|enm|sore}}, {{m|enm|sar|sār|t=very}} (from {{cog|ang|sār|t=grievous, extreme}} (Compare {{cog|de|sehr}}, {{cog|nl|zeer}}), {{cog|enm|wel|t=very}} (from {{cog|ang|wel|t=well, very}}) (Compare {{cog|de|wohl}}, {{cog|nl|wel}}, {{cog|sv|väl}}), and {{cog|enm|swith|t=quickly; very}} (from {{cog|ang|swīþe|t=very}}. More at {{m|en|warlock}}.

